Photorealistic scene of a massive world exposition at dusk in Shanghai, showing towering futuristic pavilions with dramatic angular architecture stretching toward a golden-orange sky. In the foreground, dense crowds of visitors flow like rivers between the structures, their movement blurred slightly to convey the overwhelming scale and energy. The iconic inverted red pyramid of the China Pavilion dominates the background, its latticed structure glowing warmly against the fading light. Exhausted but awestruck visitors sit on benches in the middle ground, some rubbing their feet. The scene captures both the architectural grandeur and the physical enormity of navigating such a vast exhibition space, with winding pathways disappearing into the distance between gleaming international pavilions of varied geometric shapes.
